WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.969 --> 00:00:02.969
<i>Previously...</i>

2
00:00:03.036 --> 00:00:05.369
This must reach Madame
Murray without fail.

3
00:00:05.472 --> 00:00:08.135
It is worth more than my
life. You're a soldier now.

4
00:00:08.609 --> 00:00:09.919
<i>I will not fail you. Milord.</i>

5
00:00:09.943 --> 00:00:11.221
<i>A wife who won't
let me touch her.</i>

6
00:00:11.245 --> 00:00:15.205
Admit it. You are using this
pregnancy to keep me at a distance.

7
00:00:15.482 --> 00:00:16.482
Name?

8
00:00:16.550 --> 00:00:18.815
James Malcolm Mackenzie Fraser.

9
00:00:18.886 --> 00:00:20.787
This man spared my
youngest brother's life.

10
00:00:20.854 --> 00:00:23.551
incurring a bloody
great debt of honor.

11
00:00:23.657 --> 00:00:25.537
<i>I doubt he'll live
through the journey.</i>

12
00:00:25.659 --> 00:00:26.786
Claire. she's here.

13
00:00:26.860 --> 00:00:30.729
Maybe this really... Really
can be a new beginning.

14
00:00:30.831 --> 00:00:31.831
Yes.

15
00:00:31.965 --> 00:00:32.989
- For all of us.
- Yes.

16
00:00:34.668 --> 00:00:39.163
Jamie. can you hear me?
You've come home to Lallybroch.

17
00:00:39.706 --> 00:00:41.334
Lallybroch...

18
00:00:48.982 --> 00:00:50.746
<i>Sing me a song</i>

19
00:00:50.851 --> 00:00:53.548
<i>Of a lass that is gone</i>

20
00:00:53.687 --> 00:00:56.418
<i>Say. could that lass</i>

21
00:00:56.523 --> 00:00:58.389
<i>Be I?</i>

22
00:00:59.393 --> 00:01:01.521
<i>Merry of soul</i>

23
00:01:01.595 --> 00:01:04.394
<i>She sailed on a day</i>

24
00:01:04.464 --> 00:01:06.626
<i>Over the sea</i>

25
00:01:06.733 --> 00:01:08.827
<i>To Skye</i>

26
00:01:09.836 --> 00:01:12.396
<i>Billow and breeze</i>

27
00:01:12.472 --> 00:01:14.703
<i>Islands and seas</i>

28
00:01:14.841 --> 00:01:19.279
<i>Mountains of rain and sun</i>

29
00:01:20.113 --> 00:01:22.639
<i>All that was good</i>

30
00:01:22.749 --> 00:01:24.615
<i>All that was fair</i>

31
00:01:25.452 --> 00:01:27.717
<i>All that was me</i>

32
00:01:27.788 --> 00:01:30.451
<i>Is gone</i>

33
00:01:30.557 --> 00:01:32.890
<i>Sing me a song</i>

34
00:01:32.960 --> 00:01:35.759
<i>Of a lass that is gone</i>

35
00:01:35.862 --> 00:01:37.660
<i>Say. could that lass</i>

36
00:01:38.231 --> 00:01:39.961
<i>Be I?</i>

37
00:01:40.934 --> 00:01:43.028
<i>Merry of soul</i>

38
00:01:43.103 --> 00:01:45.937
<i>She sailed on a day</i>

39
00:01:46.039 --> 00:01:49.601
<i>Over the sea</i>

40
00:01:50.143 --> 00:01:55.241
<i>To Skye</i>

41
00:01:57.000 --> 00:02:03.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

42
00:02:30.651 --> 00:02:31.928
You're sure it's
in the dovecote?

43
00:02:31.952 --> 00:02:35.650
Aye. I saw it with my own eyes.
Followed him here as he was hiding it.

44
00:02:35.722 --> 00:02:36.799
Put it in one of the nests.

45
00:02:36.823 --> 00:02:37.984
What if father catches us?

46
00:02:38.125 --> 00:02:41.118
He won't. He's round the back
milking. Now shut your gab.

47
00:02:57.210 --> 00:02:58.576
It's here. I swear.

48
00:02:59.546 --> 00:03:01.344
I swear. you're lying.

49
00:03:16.997 --> 00:03:18.056
Told you.

50
00:03:18.165 --> 00:03:20.600
It's my father's.
so I get to hold it.

51
00:03:21.768 --> 00:03:24.499
No. you're too young. and
you don't know how it works.

52
00:03:24.571 --> 00:03:25.571
You don't either.

53
00:03:27.507 --> 00:03:32.673
I've been to war. I was at Prestonpans.
I killed a filthy Redcoat officer.

54
00:03:32.979 --> 00:03:36.177
And you killed him with a
knife. aye? And it was bloody.

55
00:03:37.317 --> 00:03:39.081
Aye. bloody.

56
00:03:39.853 --> 00:03:41.879
It's much braver to
kill a man with a knife.

57
00:03:41.988 --> 00:03:43.957
Nothing but flesh and
metal between you.

58
00:03:46.860 --> 00:03:49.261
I only wish Milord
didn't send me home.

59
00:03:50.263 --> 00:03:52.027
I could've fought
at Culloden too.

60
00:03:58.705 --> 00:03:59.934
Redcoats. Hide.

61
00:04:04.544 --> 00:04:06.706
Move. cripple.

62
00:04:14.788 --> 00:04:17.087
- Father!
- It's okay. Jamie.

63
00:04:17.991 --> 00:04:20.085
Treat me as you will.
but leave the lad be.

64
00:04:20.193 --> 00:04:21.752
If you trained your
mongrels better.

65
00:04:21.828 --> 00:04:23.606
I wouldn't need to kick
them to keep them in line.

66
00:04:23.630 --> 00:04:24.630
Keep moving!

67
00:04:26.266 --> 00:04:27.290
Move!

68
00:04:28.602 --> 00:04:32.130
I'm Captain Samuel Lewis. of
his Majesty's Tenth Dragoons.

69
00:04:32.239 --> 00:04:33.468
I'm here for the Dunbonnet.

70
00:04:34.207 --> 00:04:37.439
The Dunbonnet? No one
here goes by that name.

71
00:04:39.079 --> 00:04:41.207
I should think not. openly.

72
00:04:41.615 --> 00:04:42.742
I have it on good authority

73
00:04:42.816 --> 00:04:44.751
that the notorious traitor
known as Red Jamie

74
00:04:44.818 --> 00:04:45.979
is in concealment nearabouts.

75
00:04:46.086 --> 00:04:49.682
and there's gossip in these parts
about another man called the Dunbonnet.

76
00:04:50.390 --> 00:04:53.451
We dinna get to the village
much. I canna say I've heard that.

77
00:04:53.827 --> 00:04:56.661
No? He's an outlaw
that wears a brown hat

78
00:04:56.763 --> 00:04:58.595
to cover his
distinctive red hair.

79
00:04:59.466 --> 00:05:03.460
I surmise that the Dunbonnet and
Red Jamie are one and the same.

80
00:05:06.807 --> 00:05:08.935
You tell a braw
tale there. Captain.

81
00:05:11.711 --> 00:05:14.237
James Fraser is your
brother-in-law. is he not?

82
00:05:14.314 --> 00:05:16.340
And this is his clan land?

83
00:05:16.817 --> 00:05:19.685
It was. These lands
belong to my son now.

84
00:05:20.420 --> 00:05:23.151
We've not seen nor
heard from Jamie Fraser

85
00:05:23.256 --> 00:05:26.317
since he left to fight in
the rebellion six years ago.

86
00:05:26.426 --> 00:05:29.055
Pardon me. Sir. if I don't take
you or your wife's word for it.

87
00:05:30.363 --> 00:05:34.494
I remind you that anyone who harbors
or renders aid to a Jacobite fugitive

88
00:05:34.601 --> 00:05:37.298
commits high treason and
will be hanged under law.

89
00:05:37.904 --> 00:05:42.672
Man. woman. or child.

90
00:05:45.278 --> 00:05:48.009
You're welcome to search the
house and the grounds. if you please.

91
00:05:48.081 --> 00:05:49.358
but I'll tell you
the same as I told

92
00:05:49.382 --> 00:05:52.682
Lieutenant Harding.
Captain Abbot. Major Mercer.

93
00:05:52.752 --> 00:05:56.280
and every other government officer
who comes to command these parts.

94
00:05:56.389 --> 00:05:58.756
you'll find no sign of my
traitorous brother here.

95
00:05:59.159 --> 00:06:01.560
Nor any follower of the Stuarts.

96
00:06:05.465 --> 00:06:07.696
There is a substantial
reward for information

97
00:06:07.767 --> 00:06:09.565
leading to the
capture of Red Jamie.

98
00:06:10.003 --> 00:06:14.998
so if you know of his whereabouts.
you would be wise to turn him over now.

99
00:06:19.079 --> 00:06:21.344
We canna give you what
we dinna have. Captain.

100
00:06:22.716 --> 00:06:23.716
Very well.

101
00:06:25.418 --> 00:06:27.250
Corporal MacGregor.
arrest Mr. Murray.

102
00:06:27.687 --> 00:06:30.748
Perhaps some time in the garrison's
cells will help him change his mind.

103
00:06:30.857 --> 00:06:32.826
A Scot in a Redcoat.

104
00:06:32.893 --> 00:06:34.225
You're the traitor.

105
00:06:35.128 --> 00:06:37.063
You filthy frog-eater.

106
00:06:37.130 --> 00:06:39.395
Mind your tongue
or I'll cut it out.

107
00:06:39.499 --> 00:06:42.958
Fergus. Rabbie. finish
milking and mind your chores.

108
00:06:50.710 --> 00:06:52.303
He'll be fine. mistress.

109
00:06:53.046 --> 00:06:55.914
Court's released him each
time they've seen fit to take him.

110
00:06:55.982 --> 00:06:57.927
There's no reason to think
this time's any different.

111
00:06:57.951 --> 00:07:00.716
That's a damnable shame.
Corporal MacGregor.

112
00:07:01.388 --> 00:07:02.947
Aye. a lowlander.

113
00:07:03.056 --> 00:07:05.582
Many a MacGregor
fought for the Jacobites.

114
00:07:05.759 --> 00:07:08.752
but a few fought for the
government during the '45.

115
00:07:08.862 --> 00:07:10.797
And now they think
they're better than us.

116
00:07:10.931 --> 00:07:15.164
but what the daft loons don't realize
is the British hate them just the same.

117
00:09:05.512 --> 00:09:07.981
You scared the bowels out of me.

118
00:09:21.628 --> 00:09:23.028
They've taken Ian again.

119
00:09:27.867 --> 00:09:29.631
I foolishly hoped
they were through

120
00:09:29.736 --> 00:09:33.036
when two years passed with
no Redcoats bedeviling us.

121
00:09:36.176 --> 00:09:37.610
We could go after them. Milord.

122
00:09:38.078 --> 00:09:40.877
We could slit their throats in the
night and free <i>Monsieur</i> Murray.

123
00:09:40.947 --> 00:09:42.609
Aye. That's a fine idea.

124
00:09:42.715 --> 00:09:44.555
A deed like that would
bring the whole garrison

125
00:09:44.584 --> 00:09:47.486
to Lallybroch to kill us
all. yourself included.

126
00:09:51.291 --> 00:09:54.659
I reckon every new commander
needs to make a name for himself.

127
00:09:54.894 --> 00:09:56.920
Captain Lewis was talking
about the "Dunbonnet."

128
00:09:57.864 --> 00:09:59.799
That's what they've
taken to calling you now.

129
00:09:59.899 --> 00:10:02.300
Soon enough you'll have
ballads sung in your honor.

130
00:10:07.140 --> 00:10:10.941
'Tis time to tally the rents. Ian
was just about to start on the books.

131
00:10:11.211 --> 00:10:12.771
Dinna suppose you
could do that for me.

132
00:10:16.916 --> 00:10:18.214
Brother...

133
00:10:24.424 --> 00:10:25.424
Brother!

134
00:10:26.659 --> 00:10:29.925
You ken why I can lie to
the British and feel at peace?

135
00:10:30.630 --> 00:10:32.155
It's because I'm not lying.

136
00:10:32.332 --> 00:10:35.769
James Fraser hasna been
here for a long. long time.

137
00:12:23.977 --> 00:12:25.445
Here you go.

138
00:12:25.612 --> 00:12:27.979
Ooh. whee.

139
00:12:28.181 --> 00:12:30.047
There you go.

140
00:12:30.583 --> 00:12:33.212
Now. here's bunny.

141
00:12:34.420 --> 00:12:35.420
Okay.

142
00:12:36.289 --> 00:12:39.350
Shall we see what <i>The
Globe</i> has to say today?

143
00:12:50.236 --> 00:12:52.933
"Ireland joins the
roster of free nations.

144
00:12:53.006 --> 00:12:55.976
"To the roar of guns and the
flash of fireworks in the sky.

145
00:12:56.075 --> 00:12:58.271
"the republic of
Ireland was born today."

146
00:12:58.544 --> 00:13:00.274
Sweetheart.

147
00:13:00.380 --> 00:13:03.009
This is history in the making.
You'll want to hear this.

148
00:13:04.617 --> 00:13:06.245
"The Republic.
free of British rule.

149
00:13:06.319 --> 00:13:07.319
"have to..."

150
00:13:12.558 --> 00:13:14.390
You turned over!

151
00:13:15.828 --> 00:13:17.797
All by yourself.

152
00:13:19.999 --> 00:13:20.999
You turned...

153
00:13:21.100 --> 00:13:23.092
Hot water cut out in
the middle of my shower.

154
00:13:23.169 --> 00:13:24.501
The boiler must be out again.

155
00:13:26.005 --> 00:13:27.974
What a clever girl you are.

156
00:13:28.174 --> 00:13:29.174
Why? What happened?

157
00:13:29.275 --> 00:13:32.040
She turned over. all by herself.

158
00:13:32.245 --> 00:13:33.245
Oh...

159
00:13:33.313 --> 00:13:35.009
Isn't it early for her
to be doing that?

160
00:13:36.149 --> 00:13:39.449
Well. Dr. Spock says she shouldn't
be doing it for at least another month.

161
00:13:39.519 --> 00:13:43.286
Well. what does Dr. Spock
know? Come here. come to Daddy.

162
00:13:43.356 --> 00:13:44.585
Give me a kiss.

163
00:13:44.657 --> 00:13:46.683
You're so clever. Yeah.

164
00:13:59.639 --> 00:14:00.639
- Well...
- Yeah.

165
00:14:00.707 --> 00:14:02.801
I should. uh. go
check the boiler.

166
00:15:19.719 --> 00:15:21.847
I was careful. Wasn't followed.

167
00:15:21.921 --> 00:15:24.447
Cut back on myself.
just like you taught me.

168
00:15:26.793 --> 00:15:28.421
I want to learn
to shoot. Milord.

169
00:15:33.699 --> 00:15:34.699
Where'd you get this?

170
00:15:35.935 --> 00:15:37.927
It was hidden in the dovecote.

171
00:15:39.872 --> 00:15:43.138
I want to defend our
home. I need to be ready.

172
00:15:43.543 --> 00:15:44.772
For what?

173
00:15:45.645 --> 00:15:46.738
Our next rebellion.

174
00:15:50.116 --> 00:15:51.393
There will be no next rebellion.

175
00:15:51.417 --> 00:15:52.544
But. Milord...

176
00:15:52.618 --> 00:15:54.314
No more fighting.

177
00:15:55.588 --> 00:15:58.422
Just because you're a
coward now doesn't mean I am.

178
00:16:08.301 --> 00:16:09.564
Weapons are outlawed.

179
00:16:10.102 --> 00:16:13.334
Put it back where you
found it. Don't touch it again.

180
00:16:41.400 --> 00:16:42.400
Sir.

181
00:16:43.169 --> 00:16:45.229
Dinna ken ye were
expected today.

182
00:16:53.379 --> 00:16:54.847
Came to look at the ledgers.

183
00:16:55.515 --> 00:16:56.515
Oh.

184
00:16:59.085 --> 00:17:00.246
Where's my sister?

185
00:17:03.022 --> 00:17:04.354
Dinna fash.

186
00:17:04.790 --> 00:17:08.625
The bairn had a mind to come early.
Ye'll soon have a new niece or nephew.

187
00:17:26.379 --> 00:17:27.904
The bairn is on the way.

188
00:17:28.381 --> 00:17:29.381
Aye.

189
00:17:31.117 --> 00:17:32.117
A raven!

190
00:17:33.452 --> 00:17:36.183
My granny says that ravens
are messengers of death.

191
00:17:36.989 --> 00:17:39.390
Canna be near the
house. The bairn will die!

192
00:17:44.931 --> 00:17:47.594
Bullet. Hand me the cloth.

193
00:17:50.002 --> 00:17:51.527
Ye sure that's how it works?

194
00:17:52.004 --> 00:17:54.940
Yes. I watched Murtagh
instructing the soldiers.

195
00:18:31.777 --> 00:18:34.611
I told you never
to touch this again.

196
00:18:34.680 --> 00:18:35.978
There was a raven.

197
00:18:36.082 --> 00:18:37.675
We were protecting the bairn.

198
00:18:42.321 --> 00:18:46.281
Sir. ye have a wee nephew.
He's fine and healthy.

199
00:18:59.138 --> 00:19:00.663
What were ye thinkin'. Rabbie?

200
00:19:02.675 --> 00:19:04.109
Dinna be causing
any more trouble.

201
00:19:13.252 --> 00:19:14.686
I thought I'd call him Ian.

202
00:19:15.688 --> 00:19:18.487
Time we named one after
the man that sired them?

203
00:19:26.098 --> 00:19:28.624
Ye always look braw with
a wee bairn in yer arms.

204
00:19:34.006 --> 00:19:36.532
How long's it been since
you've lain with a woman. Jamie?

205
00:19:37.009 --> 00:19:38.033
Don't...

206
00:19:40.112 --> 00:19:41.112
Janet.

207
00:19:41.180 --> 00:19:43.513
"She's dead." That's
all you ever told me.

208
00:19:44.350 --> 00:19:46.012
I dinna ken how or why.

209
00:19:47.420 --> 00:19:48.888
It's been six years now.

210
00:19:51.657 --> 00:19:53.751
Mary MacNab's still
young enough for bairns.

211
00:19:54.493 --> 00:19:57.861
I couldna run the household
without her. after Mrs. Crook died.

212
00:19:57.963 --> 00:19:59.363
and she's a fine
mother to Rabbie.

213
00:19:59.432 --> 00:20:00.661
I won't marry.

214
00:20:03.135 --> 00:20:04.194
Ever again.

215
00:20:05.538 --> 00:20:08.283
It's God's sorrow ye never had
the chance to bring a child into this...

216
00:20:08.307 --> 00:20:10.242
Maybe the bairn
should meet his brother.

217
00:20:10.409 --> 00:20:11.604
There's still time.

218
00:20:12.578 --> 00:20:13.898
Do ye hear me.
brother? I just...

219
00:20:14.246 --> 00:20:16.977
I just want you to
have some happiness!

220
00:20:21.554 --> 00:20:22.578
Find the weapon.

221
00:20:23.255 --> 00:20:24.255
Yes. Captain.

222
00:20:29.361 --> 00:20:30.795
Jenkins. move!

223
00:20:33.365 --> 00:20:34.560
Where's your mistress?

224
00:20:42.875 --> 00:20:45.811
You three. search the rooms
downstairs. MacGregor. come with me.

225
00:20:46.946 --> 00:20:48.244
Get that pistol!

226
00:20:51.417 --> 00:20:52.612
Where's the weapon?

227
00:20:52.718 --> 00:20:55.552
Weapon? We have no
weapons here. Captain.

228
00:20:55.988 --> 00:20:58.253
My scouts heard a shot
from the vicinity of this estate.

229
00:20:58.357 --> 00:21:01.384
so I ask again. Where
are you hiding the weapon?

230
00:21:01.727 --> 00:21:04.356
I canna answer for
what yer scouts heard.

231
00:21:04.430 --> 00:21:07.992
but I'll tell you again. I dinna
know of any weapons here.

232
00:21:08.100 --> 00:21:09.295
We'd never risk such a thing.

233
00:21:10.269 --> 00:21:13.103
I remind you. Madam. that as
an officer in his Majesty's army.

234
00:21:13.205 --> 00:21:17.006
I am obliged to search this house
should I have the slightest suspicion

235
00:21:17.109 --> 00:21:19.305
that the act of proscription
has been breached.

236
00:21:20.112 --> 00:21:23.571
And we will continue to do so
until you comply with my request.

237
00:21:26.385 --> 00:21:29.549
Captain. I have cooperated
with every request

238
00:21:29.622 --> 00:21:31.591
made by His Majesty's soldiers.

239
00:21:38.464 --> 00:21:40.456
Have you delivered
a child. madam?

240
00:21:42.935 --> 00:21:44.028
Aye.

241
00:21:45.604 --> 00:21:46.604
Where is it?

242
00:21:47.573 --> 00:21:48.853
Should it not be at your breast?

243
00:21:52.511 --> 00:21:53.843
It was a fearsome birth.

244
00:21:54.680 --> 00:21:56.979
and the bairn wasna
breathing when he came.

245
00:21:57.316 --> 00:22:00.775
Ye see. he was already gone.

246
00:22:01.587 --> 00:22:02.587
Good.

247
00:22:03.322 --> 00:22:05.188
It's one less teutcher
we'll have to deal with.

248
00:22:05.291 --> 00:22:06.725
Hold your tongue. Corporal.

249
00:22:09.261 --> 00:22:10.354
Where's the body?

250
00:22:11.463 --> 00:22:14.194
The midwife took it
away to clean it for burial.

251
00:22:18.537 --> 00:22:20.297
Find the midwife and
have her bring the body.

252
00:22:20.339 --> 00:22:21.339
Sir.

253
00:22:21.807 --> 00:22:23.673
Captain. please.
I canna bear it.

254
00:22:23.742 --> 00:22:25.711
Here's the pistol. Captain.

255
00:22:27.279 --> 00:22:28.303
'Tis mine.

256
00:22:29.181 --> 00:22:30.181
Yours?

257
00:22:30.916 --> 00:22:33.147
It belonged to my
late husband. Ronald.

258
00:22:33.219 --> 00:22:35.814
It was the only thing I
had left of him. so I kept it.

259
00:22:35.888 --> 00:22:39.757
It gave me comfort. Mistress
Murray knew nothing of it.

260
00:22:40.492 --> 00:22:42.484
And what occasion
did you have to fire it?

261
00:22:43.095 --> 00:22:47.999
I saw a raven land near the house
while Milady was delivering her child.

262
00:22:48.467 --> 00:22:49.992
So I shot it dead.

263
00:22:50.069 --> 00:22:52.561
Just one of the foolish
highland superstitions. sir.

264
00:22:52.938 --> 00:22:55.635
Believing a common
bird can bring ill luck.

265
00:22:56.208 --> 00:23:00.009
But it was too late. As I told
you. the bairn was born dead.

266
00:23:00.713 --> 00:23:01.713
Aye.

267
00:23:02.948 --> 00:23:05.941
Aye. I'm heart sorry. Mistress.

268
00:23:06.051 --> 00:23:07.651
Should I take her
into custody. Captain?

269
00:23:13.559 --> 00:23:15.551
We have the weapon.
She's no threat.

270
00:23:16.929 --> 00:23:18.227
But I warn you once more. madam.

271
00:23:18.697 --> 00:23:21.360
if another violation occurs.
there will be no mercy.

272
00:23:40.953 --> 00:23:42.444
Corporal. if you please!

273
00:24:04.243 --> 00:24:05.472
Thank ye. Mary. Ye did well.

274
00:24:13.752 --> 00:24:15.186
They're gone.

275
00:24:16.822 --> 00:24:19.792
This new captain. I've
seen the look of his eyes.

276
00:24:19.892 --> 00:24:21.121
He's no' one to give up.

277
00:24:21.927 --> 00:24:24.167
He'll no' stop till ye're
hanging from the end of a rope.

278
00:24:31.971 --> 00:24:33.371
Take a shovel.

279
00:24:33.472 --> 00:24:35.998
Dig a grave in the
cemetery. in case they look.

280
00:25:21.687 --> 00:25:22.687
Claire?

281
00:25:36.368 --> 00:25:37.368
What is it?

282
00:25:38.504 --> 00:25:40.097
I miss my husband.

283
00:27:05.224 --> 00:27:06.783
Go and rot. peg leg.

284
00:27:06.892 --> 00:27:08.827
Half the garrison are
searching to the north.

285
00:27:08.927 --> 00:27:10.727
and the other half are
searching to the south.

286
00:27:10.929 --> 00:27:13.797
It's only a matter of time
until we find Red Jamie.

287
00:27:13.899 --> 00:27:15.492
Then we'll be back for you.

288
00:27:16.969 --> 00:27:18.665
and yer whole family.

289
00:27:20.105 --> 00:27:21.105
Aye. well.

290
00:27:21.940 --> 00:27:23.670
it's been a lovely
visit. gentlemen.

291
00:29:05.544 --> 00:29:07.775
The brat is leading
us in circles.

292
00:29:08.347 --> 00:29:09.975
I believe he is. sir.

293
00:29:10.983 --> 00:29:11.983
You think you're smart?

294
00:29:12.351 --> 00:29:16.083
I knew you were following me.
But you can't trick me. you imbeciles.

295
00:29:17.456 --> 00:29:19.982
Tell us where Red Jamie is.

296
00:29:20.525 --> 00:29:23.188
I know that you know.
you filthy frog-eater.

297
00:29:23.262 --> 00:29:24.662
There's no Red Jamie here.

298
00:29:25.297 --> 00:29:26.297
Leave us alone!

299
00:29:26.398 --> 00:29:28.993
I'll get it out of you.
one way or another.

300
00:29:29.101 --> 00:29:31.570
You're harassing us. We
don't want you around here!

301
00:29:34.773 --> 00:29:36.571
You're all pieces of shit.

302
00:29:36.642 --> 00:29:37.735
Go to hell!

303
00:29:37.809 --> 00:29:41.075
Dirty Scotsman. You
betray your own people.

304
00:29:41.480 --> 00:29:45.576
And the Scots hate you for
it. You'll never be one of them.

305
00:29:45.651 --> 00:29:47.483
Ye brazen wee bastard.

306
00:29:53.425 --> 00:29:55.223
Your face is as
red as your coat!

307
00:29:55.494 --> 00:29:56.494
You pansies!

308
00:29:56.662 --> 00:29:57.939
I'll rip your tongue out!

309
00:29:57.963 --> 00:29:59.329
Filthy Redcoats!

310
00:29:59.431 --> 00:30:01.024
You'll pay for those words!

311
00:30:01.967 --> 00:30:05.028
That tongue will get
my boot up your ass!

312
00:30:05.237 --> 00:30:06.237
You morons!

313
00:30:06.338 --> 00:30:08.102
Don't taunt them.

314
00:30:08.173 --> 00:30:09.607
No women will have you!

315
00:30:09.675 --> 00:30:10.836
You'll be sorry.

316
00:30:10.942 --> 00:30:12.604
Get back here. ye filthy urchin!

317
00:30:12.678 --> 00:30:14.237
Run. you fool.

318
00:30:15.347 --> 00:30:17.612
French scum.
we'll string you up.

319
00:30:17.683 --> 00:30:19.311
Canna run from me!

320
00:30:25.324 --> 00:30:26.417
Hold him down!

321
00:30:26.491 --> 00:30:27.491
Go to hell!

322
00:30:32.030 --> 00:30:33.030
No!

323
00:30:33.131 --> 00:30:34.497
Wait. he's just a lad.

324
00:30:44.876 --> 00:30:46.174
Come on. leave him.

325
00:30:46.712 --> 00:30:48.510
If we do nothing. he'll die!

326
00:30:48.613 --> 00:30:50.980
That's an order. Private.

327
00:31:09.534 --> 00:31:10.729
Hold.

328
00:31:14.106 --> 00:31:16.473
Dinna be feart. Fergus. laddie.

329
00:31:16.942 --> 00:31:19.070
I watched Milady
do this many times.

330
00:31:58.517 --> 00:32:00.679
Yer quick actions
saved him. brother.

331
00:32:03.155 --> 00:32:04.248
I should have stopped them.

332
00:32:04.990 --> 00:32:07.459
Then ye'd be dead
and so would he.

333
00:32:07.793 --> 00:32:08.793
We'd all be dead.

334
00:32:19.404 --> 00:32:20.599
Brother...

335
00:32:46.465 --> 00:32:47.990
Ye all right. ye wee fool?

336
00:32:55.106 --> 00:32:56.574
I'm sorry. Milord.

337
00:32:57.008 --> 00:32:59.307
I tried to lead them
away from the cave.

338
00:32:59.845 --> 00:33:00.845
Ye did well.

339
00:33:03.482 --> 00:33:05.474
I'm the one who should be sorry.

340
00:33:13.225 --> 00:33:14.750
You remind me

341
00:33:16.461 --> 00:33:18.521
I have something to fight for.

342
00:33:23.935 --> 00:33:25.301
There you are. Milord.

343
00:33:31.810 --> 00:33:33.039
Here.

344
00:33:39.084 --> 00:33:40.143
Does it hurt much?

345
00:33:41.086 --> 00:33:42.086
A bit.

346
00:33:44.089 --> 00:33:46.524
Sometimes it feels
warm or scratchy

347
00:33:47.425 --> 00:33:49.087
or hurts like it's still there.

348
00:33:51.630 --> 00:33:52.630
But...

349
00:33:53.498 --> 00:33:56.024
Madame has been most
generous with the whiskey.

350
00:33:57.235 --> 00:34:00.000
Although. you know that I
prefer the taste of French wine.

351
00:34:09.648 --> 00:34:11.674
Do not trouble yourself. Milord.

352
00:34:12.551 --> 00:34:14.019
I have been fortunate.

353
00:34:14.886 --> 00:34:17.253
Do you recall the
agreement we made in Paris?

354
00:34:17.722 --> 00:34:19.748
When you hired me
to steal letters for you?

355
00:34:26.264 --> 00:34:27.264
Aye.

356
00:34:28.934 --> 00:34:33.030
You said. should I be
arrested or executed.

357
00:34:34.039 --> 00:34:36.304
you would have masses
said for me for a year.

358
00:34:37.776 --> 00:34:39.642
And should I lose an ear

359
00:34:42.113 --> 00:34:44.480
or a hand while
doing your service...

360
00:34:44.883 --> 00:34:49.218
That I would support
you for the rest of your life.

361
00:34:52.390 --> 00:34:53.858
You can trust me

362
00:34:55.126 --> 00:34:56.594
to keep that bargain.

363
00:34:59.097 --> 00:35:01.328
I have always
trusted you. Milord.

364
00:35:03.401 --> 00:35:04.892
I think I'm most lucky.

365
00:35:06.438 --> 00:35:07.633
In one stroke.

366
00:35:08.306 --> 00:35:10.798
I have become a
man of leisure. no?

367
00:35:20.619 --> 00:35:21.746
What do you call this again?

368
00:35:22.220 --> 00:35:23.950
It's called Eton Mess.

369
00:35:24.089 --> 00:35:27.651
Well. a cheerful term
for a failed Pavlova.

370
00:35:28.293 --> 00:35:30.455
Well. it's damn delicious.
whatever you call it.

371
00:35:30.528 --> 00:35:31.906
Maybe you could
give Millie the recipe.

372
00:35:31.930 --> 00:35:33.330
I'd be happy to.

373
00:35:33.431 --> 00:35:36.492
Now. Jerry. when was the last
time you saw me bake anything?

374
00:35:36.601 --> 00:35:39.298
If I can't find it in the
frozen section at the A&P.

375
00:35:39.371 --> 00:35:40.371
we're not having dessert.

376
00:35:40.472 --> 00:35:41.472
True. You know.

377
00:35:41.539 --> 00:35:43.217
I knew she was no Betty
Crocker when I married her.

378
00:35:43.241 --> 00:35:44.675
but her talents

379
00:35:45.076 --> 00:35:46.442
lie elsewhere.

380
00:35:46.645 --> 00:35:48.079
Stop.

381
00:35:57.088 --> 00:35:58.920
Uh. would anyone like more?

382
00:35:59.391 --> 00:36:01.292
- Heck. yeah.
- Twist my arm.

383
00:36:06.965 --> 00:36:08.485
You mind if we kill the bottle?

384
00:36:09.401 --> 00:36:10.733
Uh. it's all yours.

385
00:36:13.304 --> 00:36:14.795
Uh. well. cheers.

386
00:36:15.874 --> 00:36:17.672
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

387
00:36:25.984 --> 00:36:27.043
Nightcap?

388
00:36:29.120 --> 00:36:30.120
Please.

389
00:36:33.224 --> 00:36:37.025
So which of Millie's talents do
you think Jerry was referring to?

390
00:36:38.430 --> 00:36:40.661
Well. it's obviously

391
00:36:40.732 --> 00:36:45.830
her encyclopedic knowledge of
the complete works of Shakespeare.

392
00:36:47.005 --> 00:36:49.236
You are a snob.

393
00:36:49.574 --> 00:36:50.906
You asked the question.

394
00:38:23.768 --> 00:38:25.168
Claire. look at me.

395
00:38:27.138 --> 00:38:28.138
Baby...

396
00:38:28.807 --> 00:38:29.807
Claire. open your eyes.

397
00:38:39.984 --> 00:38:41.111
Why have you stopped?

398
00:38:44.122 --> 00:38:48.116
You... You never used to close
your eyes when we made love.

399
00:38:48.726 --> 00:38:51.719
It doesn't mean
anything. I'm enjoying this.

400
00:38:53.598 --> 00:38:54.598
Are you?

401
00:38:55.834 --> 00:38:56.961
Of course.

402
00:38:59.070 --> 00:39:00.698
Then why can't you look at me?

403
00:39:04.342 --> 00:39:05.674
Christ. Frank.

404
00:39:08.847 --> 00:39:11.646
If you're not in the
mood. you just had to say.

405
00:39:13.218 --> 00:39:14.686
Claire. when I'm with you.

406
00:39:15.820 --> 00:39:16.879
I'm with you.

407
00:39:20.058 --> 00:39:21.321
But you're with him.

408
00:39:38.910 --> 00:39:39.910
My leg.

409
00:39:41.479 --> 00:39:42.708
it's not there.

410
00:39:44.749 --> 00:39:46.718
as anyone can plainly see.

411
00:39:47.585 --> 00:39:51.283
And yet. it pains me
terrible sometimes.

412
00:39:51.956 --> 00:39:53.288
Even wakes me up at night.

413
00:39:54.659 --> 00:39:56.252
Fergus. the lad.

414
00:39:57.128 --> 00:39:59.222
he'll likely feel the
same with his hand.

415
00:40:01.699 --> 00:40:04.828
Feeling a pain in a
part of ye that's lost...

416
00:40:08.273 --> 00:40:09.941
And that's just a hand.

417
00:40:15.747 --> 00:40:17.215
Claire was yer heart.

418
00:40:52.450 --> 00:40:55.545
I thought perhaps the lad
could use another blanket.

419
00:41:01.626 --> 00:41:03.094
Who did this?

420
00:41:03.828 --> 00:41:06.889
The soldiers. when they
were searching the house.

421
00:41:07.899 --> 00:41:09.128
The Redcoats...

422
00:41:12.337 --> 00:41:15.136
They're never gonna stop
until they find the Dunbonnet.

423
00:41:22.513 --> 00:41:23.947
Turn in my own brother?

424
00:41:24.916 --> 00:41:26.636
That way. ye'll get
the reward money.

425
00:41:30.021 --> 00:41:31.319
And they'll not come after ye.

426
00:41:32.023 --> 00:41:33.582
'cause of yer
loyalty to the crown.

427
00:41:33.658 --> 00:41:35.024
To hell with the crown.

428
00:41:35.126 --> 00:41:36.924
Send word to Captain Lewis.

429
00:41:38.029 --> 00:41:39.029
Tell him...

430
00:41:42.200 --> 00:41:44.032
Tell him you heard from me.

431
00:41:44.469 --> 00:41:46.028
You know when I'll be coming.

432
00:41:46.537 --> 00:41:47.698
and when I do.

433
00:41:48.973 --> 00:41:50.464
they'll be here to arrest me.

434
00:41:50.775 --> 00:41:54.303
They'll know. once and for all.
you owe no allegiance to Red Jamie.

435
00:41:54.679 --> 00:41:56.477
Christ. man. you'll be hangit!

436
00:41:56.547 --> 00:41:58.641
I'll no' risk your lives
for me any longer.

437
00:41:58.983 --> 00:42:01.976
The British are no'
hanging Jacobites anymore.

438
00:42:02.353 --> 00:42:04.254
It's likely he'll only
be imprisoned.

439
00:42:04.355 --> 00:42:05.618
Only?

440
00:42:06.024 --> 00:42:09.825
Jamie. have ye not seen the inside
of enough prisons for one lifetime?

441
00:42:11.529 --> 00:42:14.021
Little difference to
the prison I live in now.

442
00:42:50.768 --> 00:42:52.703
Mistress Jenny has sent food.

443
00:42:54.572 --> 00:42:56.006
Do you mind the company?

444
00:42:59.877 --> 00:43:01.368
It would be welcome.

445
00:43:20.231 --> 00:43:21.722
What you did that day.

446
00:43:24.135 --> 00:43:26.127
turning the pistol
over to the Redcoats...

447
00:43:29.307 --> 00:43:30.570
It was very brave.

448
00:43:32.310 --> 00:43:34.302
'Twas the only thing I could do.

449
00:43:42.520 --> 00:43:43.920
Thank you for the barbering.

450
00:43:44.622 --> 00:43:45.988
'Twas no bother.

451
00:43:50.628 --> 00:43:51.687
I leave tomorrow.

452
00:43:53.264 --> 00:43:55.529
Ye can take the books
back to Lallybroch.

453
00:43:56.767 --> 00:43:57.962
Bury the rest.

454
00:43:58.302 --> 00:43:59.531
Stay out of sight.

455
00:43:59.937 --> 00:44:01.530
I'm gonna wash up in the river.

456
00:44:18.256 --> 00:44:19.485
Whose idea was this?

457
00:44:21.325 --> 00:44:22.623
Yours or my sister's?

458
00:44:23.394 --> 00:44:25.022
Did she think I'd
change my mind?

459
00:44:26.197 --> 00:44:27.495
Does it matter?

460
00:44:27.565 --> 00:44:28.565
No.

461
00:44:29.133 --> 00:44:31.125
It doesn't matter because
it's not gonna happen.

462
00:44:37.041 --> 00:44:38.976
If you won't leave.
then I'll have to.

463
00:44:39.477 --> 00:44:40.501
Sir.

464
00:44:42.747 --> 00:44:44.978
Your sister didna ask
me to do what I'm doin'.

465
00:44:48.486 --> 00:44:50.580
I ken well enough
what ye're thinking.

466
00:44:52.523 --> 00:44:56.324
for I saw your lady and how
it was between the two of ye.

467
00:44:59.397 --> 00:45:02.765
And it's not my mind to make
ye feel ye've betrayed that.

468
00:45:05.836 --> 00:45:08.135
What I want is to share
something different.

469
00:45:09.907 --> 00:45:11.603
Something less. mayhap.

470
00:45:14.378 --> 00:45:16.404
But something we both need.

471
00:45:20.218 --> 00:45:22.187
Something to keep us whole.

472
00:45:23.354 --> 00:45:25.380
as we move forward in this life.

473
00:45:54.752 --> 00:45:56.721
I've not done this
in a very long time.

474
00:45:57.622 --> 00:45:58.954
Neither have I.

475
00:46:36.027 --> 00:46:37.689
You can look at
me if you'd like.

476
00:46:44.669 --> 00:46:46.262
Ye're a bonny lass.

477
00:46:51.008 --> 00:46:52.567
It's just something I always do.

478
00:47:31.849 --> 00:47:35.616
<i>I threw myself into my
new role as best I could.</i>

479
00:47:38.022 --> 00:47:40.651
<i>But there was still
something missing in my life.</i>

480
00:47:42.159 --> 00:47:44.685
<i>Once. I had thought I was whole.</i>

481
00:47:45.696 --> 00:47:47.460
<i>I'd been able to love a man.</i>

482
00:47:47.732 --> 00:47:50.668
<i>to bear a child.
to heal the sick.</i>

483
00:47:51.102 --> 00:47:54.095
<i>and all these things
were natural parts of me.</i>

484
00:47:57.675 --> 00:47:59.735
<i>But the man I had
loved was Jamie.</i>

485
00:48:00.711 --> 00:48:04.842
<i>and for a time. I had been part
of something greater than myself.</i>

486
00:48:07.351 --> 00:48:08.683
<i>I wanted that again.</i>

487
00:48:09.854 --> 00:48:14.918
<i>That's why I knew. eventually. I
would need to do something more.</i>

488
00:48:18.562 --> 00:48:20.087
Can I help you. miss?

489
00:48:22.400 --> 00:48:24.426
Isn't this the
anatomy classroom?

490
00:48:24.535 --> 00:48:25.535
It is.

491
00:48:25.603 --> 00:48:28.732
Are you looking for someone?
I have a class about to start.

492
00:48:29.240 --> 00:48:30.970
You must be Dr. Simms.

493
00:48:31.308 --> 00:48:33.436
I am. And you are...

494
00:48:34.211 --> 00:48:36.407
Claire Randall. First year.

495
00:48:37.047 --> 00:48:38.047
Oh. yeah.

496
00:48:38.516 --> 00:48:42.715
The Dean informed me there was a
woman in this year's incoming class.

497
00:48:42.853 --> 00:48:44.754
A woman and a Negro.

498
00:48:45.156 --> 00:48:48.320
How very modern of us.

499
00:49:56.026 --> 00:49:57.460
Is this spot taken?

500
00:49:59.129 --> 00:50:00.495
No. it's all yours.

501
00:50:00.998 --> 00:50:02.159
Thanks.

502
00:50:07.304 --> 00:50:08.328
Joe Abernathy.

503
00:50:11.342 --> 00:50:13.675
Claire Randall.
Pleased to meet you.

504
00:50:14.245 --> 00:50:15.645
Pleased to meet you.

505
00:50:25.956 --> 00:50:27.390
All right. gentlemen.

506
00:50:29.093 --> 00:50:30.391
Let's begin.

507
00:50:32.429 --> 00:50:34.830
Bunny was wedged
behind the bed again.

508
00:50:37.868 --> 00:50:39.860
I think Bree might be
trying to tell us something.

509
00:50:51.882 --> 00:50:53.009
Good night.

510
00:50:53.517 --> 00:50:54.678
Good night.

511
00:51:28.886 --> 00:51:30.047
Jenny.

512
00:51:36.393 --> 00:51:37.393
It's me.

513
00:51:42.066 --> 00:51:43.066
I've come home!

514
00:51:52.443 --> 00:51:53.443
No. Jenny. no!

515
00:51:55.312 --> 00:51:58.476
James Alexander
Malcolm Mackenzie Fraser.

516
00:51:59.083 --> 00:52:00.574
otherwise known as Red Jamie.

517
00:52:00.951 --> 00:52:03.284
you are hereby under
arrest for high treason

518
00:52:03.354 --> 00:52:04.686
against his Majesty King George.

519
00:52:04.989 --> 00:52:05.989
Not my own sister.

520
00:52:06.090 --> 00:52:07.114
Put him in the irons!

521
00:52:07.224 --> 00:52:08.224
How could you?

522
00:52:08.325 --> 00:52:10.692
This is yer own fault!
Ye brought this on yerself!

523
00:52:11.128 --> 00:52:12.460
Well done. madam.

524
00:52:14.531 --> 00:52:16.295
You've done a
service to the crown.

525
00:52:18.302 --> 00:52:19.600
This is blood money!

526
00:52:20.137 --> 00:52:22.163
Ye gave me no choice. brother!

527
00:52:22.473 --> 00:52:25.341
And I'll never
forgive you! Never!

